On the contrary, however, if you pursue this war, as you affirm has been decreed and resolved upon by you, know that you are proclaiming war against the Immortal God like the giants, and that you will expose yourself to derision and infamy, since you will have to deal with Christ Jesus our God and His Holy Church, for whose honour and the defence of Ferrara we shall be aiding with all our powers divine and human. You will have to deal likewise with the other potentates of Italy, who will not suffer the Church of God and Italy herself to be weakened by you. You have an unjust cause, an unlawful war, you fight against God and men. We, on the contrary, maintaIn justice. Our cause is that of Christ, whose place we, however unworthy, hold upon earth. You have roused up all Italy Into a flame against you. Therefore, unless you desist frorn so great a crime and restore the places you have occupied, you will become an object of derision and even hatred to all Christians, nay, even to God Him-' seli, for all will say truly that you are the occupier of . another's property rather than the defender of your own.
